      • createDomainMapping

        default void createDomainMapping​(CreateDomainMappingRequest request,
                                 io.grpc.stub.StreamObserver<com.google.longrunning.Operation> responseObserver)
         Maps a domain to an application. A user must be authorized to administer a
 domain in order to map it to an application. For a list of available
 authorized domains, see [`AuthorizedDomains.ListAuthorizedDomains`]().

      • updateDomainMapping

        default void updateDomainMapping​(UpdateDomainMappingRequest request,
                                 io.grpc.stub.StreamObserver<com.google.longrunning.Operation> responseObserver)
         Updates the specified domain mapping. To map an SSL certificate to a
 domain mapping, update `certificate_id` to point to an `AuthorizedCertificate`
 resource. A user must be authorized to administer the associated domain
 in order to update a `DomainMapping` resource.

      • deleteDomainMapping

        default void deleteDomainMapping​(DeleteDomainMappingRequest request,
                                 io.grpc.stub.StreamObserver<com.google.longrunning.Operation> responseObserver)
         Deletes the specified domain mapping. A user must be authorized to
 administer the associated domain in order to delete a `DomainMapping`
 resource.
